"{\"uid\": \"express.co.uk-sport-othersport-1932265-why-do-olympic-athletes-bite-medals-reason-explained-after-tom-daley-chomp\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"  Sports fans may be taken aback to discover thatOlympicgold has not always been the ultimate prize in the Games.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 113, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"After the Olympics were revived in 1896, silver medals were initially given to champions.\", \"from\": 114, \"to\": 203, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"In 1904, however, they swapped silver for gold and have not looked back.\", \"from\": 205, \"to\": 277, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"That said, gold medals have not been made entirely of the substance since 1912.\", \"from\": 278, \"to\": 357, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"This makes sense given that each 529-gram medal would cost a whopping \\u00a330,000 to produce.\", \"from\": 358, \"to\": 447, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The medals on offer in Paris, valued at around \\u00a3750, have just six grams of gold in them.\", \"from\": 449, \"to\": 538, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 472, \"end\": 477, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999541419139, \"rank\": 4.585809603943568e-08, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The rest, ironically, is made out of silver, accounting for around 95 per cent of the medallion.\", \"from\": 539, \"to\": 635, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"When these medals are won, athletes have developed a habit of biting them while posing for photos.\", \"from\": 637, \"to\": 735, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"In the past, it was said this tradition stemmed from merchants who used to bite gold coins to test their purity (gold is a soft metal, so if teeth leave an indent the coin is pure), but this theory has since been debunked.\", \"from\": 736, \"to\": 958, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"David Wallechinsky, president of the International Society of Olympic Historians, revealed in 2012 the actual reason why athletes seem eager to taste the medal they have worked so hard to win.\", \"from\": 960, \"to\": 1152, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 960, \"end\": 978, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/David_Wallechinsky\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"David Wallechinsky\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/David_Wallechinsky\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/David_Wallechinsky\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"It's become an obsession with the photographers,\\\" he told CNN.\", \"from\": 1153, \"to\": 1216, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1212, \"end\": 1215, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/CNN\", \"score\": 0.9999998154987849, \"rank\": 1.3296057413510672e-07, \"text\": \"CNN\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q15265344\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/CNN\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/CNN\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I think they look at it as an iconic shot, as something that you can probably sell.\", \"from\": 1218, \"to\": 1302, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I do not think it's something the athletes would probably do on their own.\\\"\", \"from\": 1303, \"to\": 1378, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"While the origin of athletes biting their medals remains unclear, it's known that photographers often encourage them to do so for a memorable shot.\", \"from\": 1382, \"to\": 1529, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"This iconic pose, coupled with an athlete's newfound fame, makes for a perfect photo opportunity.\", \"from\": 1530, \"to\": 1627, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Tom Daley, Team GB's celebrated diver, has amassed a collection of medals throughout his career, including three bronze, one gold, and one silver.\", \"from\": 1629, \"to\": 1775, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1629, \"end\": 1638, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tom_Daley\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.1912303418023454e-39, \"text\": \"Tom Daley\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tom_Daley\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tom_Daley\"}, {\"begin\": 1640, \"end\": 1647, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain_at_the_2012_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.9335193634034533, \"rank\": 0.07078848381892917, \"text\": \"Team GB\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain_at_the_2012_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain_at_the_2012_Summer_Olympics\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He was seen obligingly biting his silver medal at this year's Games after finishing second in the 10m synchro diving final, thus completing his set of all three colours.\", \"from\": 1776, \"to\": 1945, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"A silver medal is slightly lighter than a gold one and costs half as much to produce.\", \"from\": 1947, \"to\": 2032, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Although the price of silver varies, a second-place medal would cost approximately \\u00a3380.\", \"from\": 2033, \"to\": 2121, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"We use your sign-up to provide content in ways you have consented to and to improve our understanding of you.\", \"from\": 2123, \"to\": 2232, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"This may include adverts from us and 3rd parties based on our understanding.\", \"from\": 2233, \"to\": 2309, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"You can unsubscribe at any time.\", \"from\": 2310, \"to\": 2342, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Read ourPrivacy Policy  A bronze medal, made mostly of copper, reportedly costs just over \\u00a310 to make but its value to those who earn it is immeasurable.\", \"from\": 2343, \"to\": 2496, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Observers may have spotted an iron hexagon at the centre of each medal.\", \"from\": 2497, \"to\": 2568, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"This design element, introduced at the Paris Games, was inspired by France's nickname, L'Hexagone.\", \"from\": 2569, \"to\": 2667, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2637, \"end\": 2643, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9997472176246256, \"rank\": 0.00024139255728882188, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}, {\"begin\": 2656, \"end\": 2666, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Metropolitan_France\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"L'Hexagone\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Metropolitan_France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Metropolitan_France\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The material for the hexagon was sourced from a piece of the iconic Eiffel Tower.\", \"from\": 2668, \"to\": 2749, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"SEARCH  CONNECT WITH US  TODAY'S PAPER  See today's front and back pages, download the newspaper, order back issues and use the historic Daily Express newspaper archive.\", \"from\": 2751, \"to\": 2920, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2888, \"end\": 2901, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Daily_Express\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.78685900466041e-19, \"text\": \"Daily Express\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\", \"Q234460\", \"Q11032\", \"Q1092563\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Daily_Express\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Daily_Express\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"EXPRESS.CO.UK  Daily Express uses notifications to keep you updated\", \"from\": 2922, \"to\": 2989, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2937, \"end\": 2950, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Daily_Express\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.78685900466041e-19, \"text\": \"Daily Express\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\", \"Q234460\", \"Q11032\", \"Q1092563\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Daily_Express\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Daily_Expres